<!--
README
======
Title: Md. Riday Howlader — Research Website
Description: Personal research website and academic portfolio of Md. Riday Howlader – focusing on International Relations, Refugee Studies, Geopolitics, and Migration.
Repo: mdridayhowladerbu-a11y
License: MIT

How to use
----------
1. Save this file as `index.html` in the root of your repository.
2. Preview locally by opening it in a browser, or push to GitHub and enable GitHub Pages (Settings -> Pages -> Source: main / gh-pages).
3. To split into files, extract <style> into styles.css and <script> into scripts.js.
4. Customize content inside <main id="content"> sections.

Accessibility notes
-------------------
- Skip link to bypass navigation for keyboard users.
- Semantic HTML (header, nav, main, footer, article, section).
- ARIA labels where helpful and landmarks for screen readers.
- High-contrast focus outline and ``prefers-reduced-motion`` support.
- Accessible contact form (labels, aria-required, validation hints) though not hooked to a backend.

-->

